ry -- real canary rollback is T088, 14-day soak is T089 -- and that Cloudflare D1 Time Travel is not claimed), adversarial_review.md. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S8-P01-T086/test-results/dr_drill_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): the isolated drill completes and is consistent across all 6 components, 0 release blockers. Every component's recoverable compares the re-derivation to a COMMITTED known point (recovery_known_points.json for content_bundle/r2/d1, plus the committed registry_hash / worker build_id / baselines report) -- never a same-run self-comparison -- so a code/input drift flips it to a release blocker; a 4-lens adversarial review caught and fixed an initial content/r2 self-comparison vacuity. 3 load-bearing negative controls fire (flipping one source's enabled makes the registry recompile diverge from d63cf6bd; a content-bundle input drift makes the render hash diverge from b70fe73e; a different R2 content makes the key diverge from the committed key -- each flips recoverable False and is classified a release blocker; also the worker + registry source files are byte-immutable across the drill). Realtime not regressed (NOT deployed; live build b189d3cc0703). Cost (unknown != 0): production 0 (NOT_DEPLOYED, all local tmp/in-memory); 1 read-only GET. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
